news.title: Ahmedabad: Iscon-Ambli stretch sees Rs 1,500 crore land transactions in past year
news.para: In fact, the high street saw some fast and furious real estate action following the ebbing of second wave of pandemic with the four kilometre stretch from Iscon Crossroads to Bopal Junction recording at least a dozen major land transactions worth Rs 1,500 crore in the past year.

news.title: Gurugram: Mahira Homes buyers stage protest, seek flat possession
news.para: More than 1,500 homebuyers, most of whom have already paid 100% of the amount, have been left in the lurch since DTCP cancelled the licence of the project and recommended registration of an FIR against Mahira Infratech Pvt Ltd for “forging documents and fabricating bank guarantees”.

news.title: As work on Noida airport takes off, 'dream houses' & illegal plots offered around site
news.para: The business, often illegal, is lucrative. Dealers are trying to lure prospective buyers with claims that the properties are authorised by the Yamuna Expressway Industrial Development Authority (YEIDA) or that they aren’t part of the area notified for industrial development.

news.title: Noida authority to tweak land policy for group housing
news.para: Developers in the city that has seen a ballooning trend of unfinished projects and mounting dues owed by builders will not be allotted the land until they pay 100% of the amount to the authority, officials said on Sunday.

news.title: Prestige Group to invest Rs 7,500 crore to develop 16 million sq ft in Mumbai
news.para: “With the state recording the highest GST collections in India and contributing to 15% of GST of the overall Indian economy, Mumbai has established itself as the leading commercial hub in India. We look forward to establishing our presence in the western region through Mumbai,” Irfan Razack, CMD, Prestige Group, told ET.

news.title: Navi Mumbai civic body declares 514 buildings dangerous
news.para: As many as 61 buildings across city nodes fall under the C-1 category (high risk and uninhabitable-redevelopment is the only option) which need to be vacated and demolished immediately.

news.title: MDDA to take action on over 600 illegal structures identified in Dehradun
news.para: In a meeting of senior agency officials with state minister Premchand Aggarwal on Friday, instructions were given to the staff to speed up steps against illegal construction.

news.title: Telangana HC stops apartment association from taking coercive action against owners
news.para: A vacation bench of the Telangana high court has issued a notice to an apartment association asking it to explain its stand on a petition filed by some flat owners questioning the action of the association stopping essential services to them.

news.title: Delhi: 14 years on, Kathputli Colony residents yet to get homes
news.para: It was expected that the first batch of around 500 flats in the completed apartment blocks would be handed over by March 31, 2022. The rest of the apartments were expected to be allotted by the end of this year.

news.title: No upkeep fee till audit, say Chintels Paradiso residents
news.para: Two residents died in a vertical collapse of living rooms at Tower D of the society on February 10. Residents have also asked the developer to avoid unauthorised usage of the Rs 15 crore they deposited as interest-free maintenance security (IFMS) funds and electricity infrastructure charges at the time of buying a property there.

news.title: Government seeks to cool down steel, plastic and cement prices
news.para: Finance minister Nirmala Sitharaman said measures are afoot to improve the availability and price of cement, through better logistics.

news.title: JK Cement plans to raise up to Rs 500 crore via NCDs
news.para: The fund raising will be at an interest rate that will be determined by the prevailing money market conditions at the time of borrowing, said JK Cement in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body mulls over 'no-dues certificate' to check growth of illegal buildings
news.para: The proposal will be presented before MC general house meeting as asked by mayor Balkar Singh Sandhu, who wanted other members of the house to give suggestions and approve the same.

news.title: Mumbai: Nine years since eviction suit filed, tenant yet to vacate; court gives two months
news.para: Allowing a 77-year-old Grant Road building landlord’s plea to evict his 48-year-old tenant, the court said the latter did nothing in the nine years since the court was moved.

news.title: Pay Rs 10,000 a day if flat not handed over: MahaRERA
news.para: The penalty will be doubled every month of the default, said the order passed on April 25 by Vijay Satbir Singh, member of MahaRERA, noting that no one has appeared for the builder during the hearing via videoconferencing.
